[1] Case update
- Wed 22 Aug 2018. Epidemiological situation report, 21 Aug 2018, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=28c56ccc4a

- A total of 103 cases of haemorrhagic fever were reported in the region, 76 confirmed and 27 probable.
- 7 suspected cases are under investigation.
- 1 new case confirmed to Mabalako who is a care provider.
- 2 deaths of confirmed cases in Mabalako

News of the response
International collaboration
---------------------------
- The Ambassador of the European Union to the Democratic Republic of Congo, Mr Bart Ouvry, the Deputy Special Representative of the UN Secretary-General in the DRC, Mrs Kim Bolduc, and the Minister-Counselor for Development Cooperation at the Embassy of Belgium, Ms Annelies De Backer, traveled to Beni on Wed 22 Aug 2018. After meeting the teams leading the Ebola response at headquarters, they went to Beni's General Referral Hospital where they visited Ebola treatment center.

Vaccination
-----------
- Since vaccination began on 8 Aug 2018, 2179 people have been vaccinated, including 1178 in Mabalako, 552 in Beni, and 449 in Mandima.
- The vaccination of contacts of the 1st confirmed case of Oicha began this Wed 22 Aug 2018.

[Oicha is a city in North Kivu province, in eastern DRC.
The number of vaccinees has increased impressively since yesterday, 21 Aug 2018, when 1693 people had been vaccinated; today 2179 -- good progress being made. - Mod.LK]

